    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Rhinopithecus bieti (Primates: Cercopithecidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573597>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573599>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573603>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573605>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573607>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573609> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573597>
    dc:description "Fig.1.—An adult male and ajuvenileRhinopithecus bieti. Photographed at Tacheng in the Baimaxueshan (White Horse Snow Mountain) Nature Reserve,Yunnan, China by L. E. Harding." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573597/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573599>
    dc:description "Fig. 2.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of skull and lateral view of mandibles of Rhinopithecus bieti: female (right), KIZ [Kunming Institute of Zoology] #210529 and male (left), KIZ #210823. Photographs by Lianxian Han and Ben Han used with permission." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573599/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573603>
    dc:description "Fig. 3.—Rhinopithecus bieti is restricted to ridge-top “islands” of forest between the Mekong and Yangtze rivers in Yunnan and Xizang provinces, China. Study areas mentioned in the text are shown. Not all groups are shown, but all are included within the ovals representing genetically distinct clusters (see “Distribution”) except for the Mt. Wubao group, which has not been sampled." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573603/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573605>
    dc:description "Fig. 4.—Rhinopithecus bieti habitat in Baimaxueshan (White Horse Snow Mountain) National Nature Reserve with Jinsha Jiang (Yangtze River) in foreground. Photograph by L. E. Harding." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573605/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573607>
    dc:description "Fig. 5.—An adult male Rhinopithecus bieti eating lichen. Photograph by L. E. Harding." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573607/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573609>
    dc:description "Fig. 6.—Adult male, adult female, and immature Rhinopithecus bieti (shown left to right). The immature individual is grooming the female, who is lying on her back (note the ischial callosities of the female). Photograph by L. E. Harding." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573609/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

